---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Our Teas">
  <section class="tea-collection">

    <article class="tea-item">
      <h2 class="tea-name">Forager’s Delight</h2>
      <p class="tea-origin">Origin: Liugui, Kaohsiung, Taiwan | Altitude: 1,400 metres above sea level</p>
      <p class="tea-scene">Early spring in the forest, soft light through the canopy.</p>
      <p class="tea-description">
        Foraged from wild <em>Camellia formosensis</em>, this delicate white tea offers a silky infusion with hints of mint, cinnamon, and warm earth. Ideal for languorous mornings or quiet afternoon walks.
      </p>
      <p class="tea-pairing">
        <strong>Seasonal pairing:</strong> Steamed white fish with herbs, fresh goat’s cheese, or spring greens and sesame.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="tea-item">
      <h2 class="tea-name">Winter Harvest</h2>
      <p class="tea-origin">Origin: Mingjian, Nantou, Taiwan | Altitude: 300–600 metres above sea level</p>
      <p class="tea-scene">Autumn air, windows cracked, the scent of fallen leaves.</p>
      <p class="tea-description">
        Grown in red laterite soil and picked in the cooler months, this <em>Sijichun</em> oolong is naturally sweet, floral, and silky. A gently restorative tea to clear the air.
      </p>
      <p class="tea-pairing">
        <strong>Seasonal pairing:</strong> Roasted pumpkin, soba noodles with sesame oil, or spiced poached pears.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="tea-item">
      <h2 class="tea-name">Sweet Pearls</h2>
      <p class="tea-origin">Origin: Alishan, Chiayi, Taiwan | Altitude: 800–1,000 metres above sea level</p>
      <p class="tea-scene">Summer afternoons, golden light, laughter in the background.</p>
      <p class="tea-description">
        This <em>Jin Xuan</em> milk oolong from Alishan is creamy and light, with notes of sweet popcorn, toasted grain, and molasses. Joyful and comforting, with a soft finish.
      </p>
      <p class="tea-pairing">
        <strong>Seasonal pairing:</strong> Buttered corn, grilled peaches, or almond cookies.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="tea-item">
      <h2 class="tea-name">Icy Peak</h2>
      <p class="tea-origin">Origin: Lugu, Nantou, Taiwan | Altitude: 600–800 metres above sea level</p>
      <p class="tea-scene">Deep winter evening, vinyl playing low, soft wool, warm hands.</p>
      <p class="tea-description">
        A roasted <em>Dong Ding</em> oolong that’s smoky and full-bodied, with a long, warming finish. Notes of honey, cacao, and ripe melon unfold slowly over each infusion.
      </p>
      <p class="tea-pairing">
        <strong>Seasonal pairing:</strong> Dark chocolate, braised meats, or roasted chestnuts.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="tea-item">
      <h2 class="tea-name">Amber Twists</h2>
      <p class="tea-origin">Origin: Lalashan, Taoyuan, Taiwan | Altitude: 1,600 metres above sea level</p>
      <p class="tea-scene">Late summer dusk, mist curling through old trees.</p>
      <p class="tea-description">
        Fully fermented and grown beneath Lalashan’s forest canopy, this tea opens with a dry, woodsy note before revealing mellow orchard fruit and soft cypress warmth.
      </p>
      <p class="tea-pairing">
        <strong>Seasonal pairing:</strong> Grilled plums, mushroom broth, or aged cheese.
      </p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <style>
    .tea-collection {
      font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
      color: #b2d8c8; /* soft green base */
      line-height: 1.7;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .tea-item {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #325144;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .tea-name {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #e6fbf1; /* primary light green accent */
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .tea-origin {
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: #a0cabc;
    }

    .tea-scene {
      font-weight: 500;
      color: #d1f5e3;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .tea-description {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: #c1e8da;
    }

    .tea-pairing {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: #aee7d0;
    }

    .tea-pairing strong {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #e6fbf1;
    }

    em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: #e6fbf1;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>